	<h2>EXTENDED SCHOOL CLOSURE INFORMATION</h2>
<p><strong>Milford Schools are closed through the end of the school year. </strong></p>
<p><strong>Distance learning will continue until May 28 for grades preschool through 11th.</strong></p>
<p><strong>This page will serve as a hub of information during this extended school closure and will be updated continually.</strong><br><br></p>
<table style="height: 409px; width: 265px; float: left;" width="64" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5"><tbody>
<tr>
<td><a href="/services-and-programs/extended-school-closure-information-20/latest-news-35/"><span class="tinymce-btn-styles">LATEST NEWS</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/services-and-programs/extended-school-closure-information-20/faq-36/"><span class="tinymce-btn-styles">FAQ</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/services-and-programs/extended-school-closure-information-20/online-learning-resources-37/"><span class="tinymce-btn-styles">ONLINE RESOURCES</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/services-and-programs/extended-school-closure-information-20/food-pick-up-38/"><span class="tinymce-btn-styles">FOOD PICK UP</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/services-and-programs/extended-school-closure-information-20/contact-us-39/"><span class="tinymce-btn-styles">CONTACT US</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/services-and-programs/extended-school-closure-information-20/health-resources-40/"><span class="tinymce-btn-styles">HEALTH RESOURCES</span></a></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">All school buildings are closed for the rest of the school year. All athletic facilities are closed. This necessary action was taken to prevent widespread infection of the coronavirus.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Classroom instruction cannot be replaced by online or distance learning. The relationship built between teachers and students serves as the needed foundation of deeper learning. The classroom experience for a student cannot easily be replicated by virtual or distance learning. However, in a time like this, at-home learning is our only option, and we will continue. </p>
<p dir="ltr">We know the Governor’s order to close schools for an even longer period of time presents a challenge for our families. Although our buildings will remain closed, learning will continue. Our teachers will continue to communicate with students. </p>
<p><a href="/services-and-programs/extended-school-closure-information-20/faq-36/">Please click here for more details.</a> </p>
